				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$x,y\in {{\mathbb{R}}}^{t}$$\end{document}x,y∈ℝt. Pairwise FC, measuring the statistical dependence between all possible pairs in a given network would yield a matrix of size n × n. This would generate a symmetric matrix and can be reduced to \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
