Euclidean distance is a dissimilarity measure and one of the more commonly used metrics due to the well-studied background of Euclidean spaces. It is easy to conceptualize and intuitive as it measures the geometric distance between two points. In case of vectors, this can be computed by the following:6\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
